 Jewish Magical and Mystical Traditions on the Artificial Anthropoid\", New York: SUNY Press, 1990.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"Hasidism: Between Ecstasy and Magic\", New York: SUNY Press, 1995.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"Kabbalistic Prayer and Color, Approaches to Judaism in Medieval Times\", D. Blumenthal, ed., Chicago: Scholar's Press, 1985.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"The Mystica Experience in Abraham Abulafia\", New York, SUNY Press, 1988.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"Kabbalah: New Perspectives, New Haven\", Yale University Press, 1988.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"Magic and Kabbalah in the 'Book of the Responding Entity\"'; The Solomon Goldman Lectures VI, Chicago: Spertus College of Judaica Press, 1993.\nBULLET::::- Idel, Moshe; \"The Story of Rabbi Joseph della Reina\"; Behayahu, M. \"Studies and Texts on the History of the Jewish Community in Safed\".\nBULLET::::- Kaplan, Aryeh; \"Inner Space: Introduction to Kabbalah, Meditation and Prophecy\". Moznaim Publishing Corp 1990.\nBULLET::::- McGiney, John W.; \"'The Written' as the Vocation of Conceiving Jewishly\"\nBULLET::::- Samuel, Gabriella; \"The Kabbalah Handbook: A Concise Encyclopedia of Terms and Concepts in Jewish Mysticism\". Penguin Books 2007.\nBULLET::::- Scholem, Gershom; \"Major Trends in Jewish Mysticism\", 1941.\nBULLET::::- Scholem, Gershom; \"Jewish Gnosticism, Merkabah Mysticism, and the Talmudic Tradition\", 1960.\nBULLET::::- Scholem, Gershom; \"Sabbatai Zevi, the Mystical Messiah\", 1973.\nBULLET::::- Scholem, Gershom; \"Kabbalah\", Jewish Publication Society, 1974.\nBULLET::::- Wineberg, Yosef; \"Lessons in Tanya: The Tanya of R. Shneur Zalman of Liadi\" (5 volume set). Merkos L'Inyonei Chinuch, 1998.\nBULLET::::- Wirszubski, Chaim; \"Pico della Mirandola's Encounter with Jewish Mysticism\", Harvard University Press, 1989.\nBULLET::::- Wolfson, Elliot; \"Through a Speculum That Shines: Vision and Imagination in Medieval Jewish Mysticism\", Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1994.\nB