ust for Life: On the Writings of Kathy Acker\", ed. Carla Harryman, Avital Ronell, and Amy Scholder (Verso, 2006)\nBULLET::::- \"Kathy Acker and Transnationalism\", ed. Polina Mackay and Kathryn Nicol (Cambridge Scholars, 2009)\nBULLET::::- \"I'm Very into You: Correspondence 1995--1996\", by Kathy Acker and McKenzie Wark, edited by Matias Viegener (Semiotext(e), 2017)\nBULLET::::- \"After Kathy Acker: A Literary Biography\", by Chris Kraus (Semiotext(e), 2017)\nBULLET::::- Pérez, Rolando. \"What is Don Quijote/Don Quixote And…And…And the Disjunctive Synthesis of Cervantes and Kathy Acker\", Cervantes ilimitado: cuatrocientos años del Quijote. Ed. Nuria Morgado. ALDEEU, 2016. pp. 75–100.\n\nBULLET::::- \"Part 2\" · \"Part 3\"\nBULLET::::- Acker interview with the Spice Girls.\nBULLET::::- \"Kathy Acker Papers, 1972–1997 and undated\", at Duke University\n"}
